  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Clarifying The Requirements**\n\nI\'m focusing on the user\'s explicit instructions, specifically \"Build me an angular app with screens that look like this,\" while noting the hotlinking of images. I\'m also cross-referencing this against the current development environment as described in the metadata.json. This could present a challenge and needs further evaluation.\n\n\n**Analyzing The Development Environment**\n\nI see a React environment with Vite, Tailwind CSS, and other React-specific dependencies. My initial confusion about the Angular request stemmed from the user\'s instructions. However, the existing setup dictates a React-based solution. I\'m now focused on delivering a React app that fulfills the user\'s visual requirements, possibly simulating an Angular-like dashboard. The key is strict adherence to the provided specifications, nothing more, nothing less.\n\n\n**Interpreting User Intent**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the core of this task: building a high-fidelity React app. The user\'s initial mention of \"Angular\" seems to be a point of confusion; the React framework guidelines are explicit. I\'m focusing on \"Build and Modify Code,\" and ensuring that the visual designs provided, particularly the \"Decision Tables\" (Fraud Detection Rules) screen, are perfectly replicated, along with other specifications. I am working to determine the intent and build the design, nothing more, nothing less.\n\n\n**Defining UI Elements**\n\nI\'m now breaking down the user interface components. I am planning the \"IF/THEN\" tabular editor, then the visual rule builder (\"Rule Designer\"), the execution logs (\"History\"), the rule orchestrator (DAG), and configuration screens. I\'m focusing on the distinct visual and interactive elements for each, ensuring they align with the described functionality.\n\n\n**Expanding Feature Scope**\n\nI\'m now identifying additional features. I am updating \"Identity & Ownership\" screens with toggle-able items for cache TTL, send-back data, lifecycle status, and connectors. I\'m focusing on \"Rule Configuration\" with resource tags and Slack alert tasks. I\'m thinking of this as a complete Logic/Rule Engine product. I\'m evaluating the `gemini-api`, although AI isn\'t explicitly requested, but it could enable features like a \"Generate Rule\" tool. I\'ll maintain a client-only or server-side-api (if needed) for highly interactive, polished app.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 7
      nanos: 524054570
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
