  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Exploring Typography Options**\n\nI\'m currently investigating how to customize typography themes within Tailwind CSS. Specifically, I\'m focusing on the implementation details and wondering about compatibility with Tailwind v4, where `@theme` might be used for variable definition. I\'m also examining typography specifications within the Institutional Precision and Logic Infrastructure, starting with its source.\n\n\n**Defining Font and Color Schemes**\n\nI\'ve decided on the fonts: Source Serif 4, Source Sans 3 (or Inter as a fallback), and JetBrains Mono. I\'m importing them from Google Fonts now. Also, I\'ve listed the custom colors from the Institutional Precision and Logic Infrastructure: surface-container-low, surface-container-lowest, surface, background, primary, secondary, on-surface, outline-variant, and outline. I\'m now crafting the CSS.\n\n\n**Structuring React State**\n\nI\'m now focusing on organizing React state for the engine components. I\'ve realized keeping everything in one file is problematic. My solution is a modular approach: `src/types.ts` for data types, `src/components/Sidebar.tsx`, `DecisionTable.tsx`, `RuleSets.tsx`, `RuleCanvas.tsx`, `HistoryLogs.tsx`, and `RuleConfig.tsx` for distinct component state management.\n\n\n"
