  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing Functions View**\n\nI\'ve been examining the `Functions.tsx` file and see a straightforward Functions view. There\'s a sidebar that presents a static list of functions. The main section is divided into Function Overview, Parameter Configuration, and Run Function Evaluation Test areas. Next, I plan to consider how each part interacts with the others.\n\n\n**Exploring Feature Enhancements**\n\nI\'m now diving into the user\'s provided snippets for \"Functions Library\" and \"Function Builder.\" I\'ve identified key areas: filtering, aggregation, and record selection. \"Functions Library\" lists filter options and aggregation types. The \"Function Builder\" wizard shows configurations for sorting, selecting, and aggregation functions, including input config, filter logic, sorting order, and mathematical operations for each respective function. This seems quite robust and well thought out!\n\n\n**Designing Function Integration**\n\nI\'m now thinking about integrating the \"Logic Summary\" and \"Output Signature\" previews into `Functions.tsx`. I\'m envisioning a `currentView` state, which drives the main view: \"library\" for the function library, and a wizard to help with addition. The wizard would include steps: Input Config, Filter Logic, and Sort/Select (covering sorting, selecting, and record range).\n\n\n**Refining Function Wizard Steps**\n\nI\'ve been further refining the Function Wizard steps, aiming for optimal user flow. Input Config, Filter Logic, and Sort/Select are set. Now, I\'m focusing on \"Aggregate\" step, which completes the wizard. Users choose mathematical operations, like Sum or Average, for a target field. I can see the dynamic \"Logic Summary\" and output signature, which is very helpful. Saving adds the new function.\n\n\n**Validating UI Implementation**\n\nI\'ve tested the Functions Library list and verified dynamic client-side persistence; no mocks needed! It seamlessly adds, allows editing and testing. I\'m focusing on the visual style now. The HTML snippets had Tailwind with good colors and Lucide or Google Material Symbols. I need to convert the Google Material Symbols to `lucide-react` icons. I\'m mapping them, for example, `schema` to `Database` or `Shield`.\n\n\n"
